[
    {
        "content": "<p>I have a syntax category in which I would like to use equality symbols. For some reason, however, <code>macro_rules</code> does not think I should use them. Instead I get the error <code>unexpected token ']'; expected '='</code>. Why does this happen and how to solve this?</p>\n<p>MWE:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">declare_syntax_cat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">eq</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">syntax</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">term</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\" = \"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">term</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">eq</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">syntax</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"[eq|\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">eq</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"]\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">term</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">my_eq</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Prop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">macro_rules</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"o\">([</span><span class=\"n\">eq</span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">$</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">term</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">$</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">term</span><span class=\"o\">])</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">my_eq</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">$</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">$</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 440481846,
        "sender_full_name": "Ira Fesefeldt",
        "timestamp": 1716546540
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The issue is that the <code>term</code> on the LHS is consuming the <code>=</code>, because that already is valid as a <code>term</code></p>",
        "id": 440487033,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1716548759
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(Separately, you probably want <code> `(term| [eq| $a:term = $b:term]) </code> to remind lean what category you are trying to match)</p>",
        "id": 440487463,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1716548879
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah. I see. Thanks for the explanation!</p>",
        "id": 440488080,
        "sender_full_name": "Ira Fesefeldt",
        "timestamp": 1716549089
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And the way to solve that is to increase the precedence, <code>syntax term:51 \" = \" term:51 : eq</code></p>",
        "id": 440500864,
        "sender_full_name": "Sebastian Ullrich",
        "timestamp": 1716554277
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"310045\">@Eric Wieser</span> <code>term</code> is the default category</p>",
        "id": 440500934,
        "sender_full_name": "Sebastian Ullrich",
        "timestamp": 1716554288
    }
]